---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'March 10, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - FreeAIToolz"
  description="Privacy Policy for FreeAIToolz. Learn how we handle your data, what we collect, and how we protect your privacy."
  keywords="privacy policy, FreeAIToolz privacy, data protection"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-gray-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 prose-custom">
      <p>This Privacy Policy describes how FreeAIToolz ("we," "us," or "our"), operated by AI2Flows, collects, uses, and protects information when you use our website at freeaitoolz.com (the "Service"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your data transparently in compliance with applicable international privacy laws including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and other relevant data protection regulations.</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
      <p>When you use our tools, you may input text content (such as text to humanize, detect, paraphrase, or analyze). This text is processed in real-time to deliver tool results and is <strong>not stored, saved, or logged</strong> on our servers after processing is complete. We do not require you to create an account, provide your name, email address, or any other personal information to use our tools.</p>

      <h3>1.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>When you visit our website, we may automatically collect certain technical information, including your IP address (anonymized where possible), browser type and version, operating system, referring URL, pages visited and time spent on each page, device type (desktop, mobile, tablet), and general geographic location (country/region level only). This information is collected through standard web analytics tools and is used solely for website performance optimization and aggregate usage analytics.</p>

      <h3>1.3 Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
      <p>We use essential cookies necessary for the website to function properly and analytics cookies (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors use our website. You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings. We do not use tracking cookies for advertising purposes on our own tools, though third-party advertising partners (such as Google AdSense) may use cookies to serve relevant advertisements.</p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use the collected information to provide and maintain our free tools, analyze website usage to improve user experience, ensure website security and prevent abuse, display relevant advertisements through Google AdSense, and comply with legal obligations. We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. We do <strong>not</strong> use your tool input data for training AI models. We do <strong>not</strong> create user profiles from tool usage data.</p>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>Our Service integrates with the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Anthropic (Claude AI)</strong> — Powers our AI tools. Text you input is sent to Anthropic's API for processing. Anthropic's privacy policy governs their handling of this data. Anthropic does not use API inputs to train their models.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — Collects anonymized website usage data. Governed by Google's Privacy Policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — Displays advertisements. May use cookies to serve relevant ads. Governed by Google's Privacy Policy.</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — Hosts our website. Governed by Vercel's Privacy Policy.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>Tool input data (text you submit) is processed in real-time and <strong>not retained</strong> after the response is delivered. Analytics data is retained in aggregated, anonymized form for up to 26 months. Server logs may be retained for up to 30 days for security purposes.</p>

      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of Access</strong> — Request information about data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Rectification</strong> — Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Erasure</strong> — Request deletion of your data</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing</strong> — Request limitation of data processing</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Data Portability</strong> — Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Object</strong> — Object to data processing based on legitimate interests</li>
        <li><strong>Right to Withdraw Consent</strong> — Withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@freeaitoolz.com">privacy@freeaitoolz.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>6. GDPR Compliance (EU/EEA Users)</h2>
      <p>For users in the European Union and European Economic Area, we process data under the following legal bases: legitimate interest (website analytics and security), consent (cookies and advertising), and contract performance (providing the requested tool services). Our data processing activities are designed to comply with the GDPR. If you believe we have not adequately addressed your data protection concerns, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local Data Protection Authority.</p>

      <h2>7. CCPA Compliance (California Users)</h2>
      <p>California residents have additional rights under the CCPA including the right to know what personal information is collected and how it is used, the right to request deletion of personal information, the right to opt-out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell personal information), and the right to non-discrimination for exercising CCPA rights.</p>

      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Our Service is not directed to individuals under the age of 13 (or 16 in the EU). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will take steps to delete such information.</p>

      <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>Your information may be processed in countries other than your country of residence (including the United States). We ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place for international data transfers in accordance with applicable data protection laws.</p>

      <h2>10. Security</h2>
      <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information, including HTTPS encryption for all data transmission, secure API communications with third-party services, and regular security assessments. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.</p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, contact us at:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@freeaitoolz.com">privacy@freeaitoolz.com</a></li>
        <li>Website: <a href="https://www.ai2flows.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.ai2flows.com</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>